this portion of the Wyoming regulations (Administrative Record No. WY&hyph;21&hyph;11).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
3. The U.S. Department of Agriculture_Soil Conservation Service commented that the SCS supports the proposed rule
amendment and feels that it is quite workable (Administrative Record Nos. WY&hyph;21&hyph;9, WY&hyph;21&hyph;24,
and WY&hyph;21&hyph;66).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
4. U.S. Department of Agriculture_Forest Service_Rocky Mountain Region commented that the proposed rule plan is
well written and well thought out. They additionally suggested that weed free native hay be required rather than preferred
as proposed in Appendix A (Administrative Record No. WY&hyph;21&hyph;13). As previously noted, neither the proposed
rule nor the modification to the appendix can be approved. Therefore, the suggested requirements for weed free native
hay becomes moot to this rulemaking action.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
5. U.S. Department of Agriculture_Agricultural Research Service_Northern Plains Area recommended changes to
the proposed rules and appendix. As discussed in Finding 6, the Director is not approving the proposed rules and appendix.
Thus changes to them need not be discussed at this time (Administrative Record No. WY&hyph;21&hyph;10).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
6. The U.S. Department of Interior_U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service (USFWS or the Service) provided substantial comments
on February 16, April 14, and November 22, 1993 (Administrative Record Nos. WY&hyph;21&hyph;5, WY&hyph;21&hyph;19,
and WY&hyph;21&hyph;64). The comments supported the proposed rules and appendix but not the statutory language.
They additionally recommended several changes to the proposed rules. As discussed above, the majority of the proposed
rules conflict with the statutory language and OSM is not approving either the proposed rules or statutory provisions.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
7. The U.S. Department of Interior_Bureau of Land Management (BLM) provided substantial comments on March 10 and
December 3, 1993 (Administrative Record Nos. WY&hyph;21&hyph;15 and WY&hyph;21&hyph;67). Again the comments
supported the proposed rules and appendix, therefore discussion of BLM's comments would be of no merit.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
State Historic Preservation Office (SHPO) and Advisory Council on Historic Preservation (ACHP) Comments
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

