<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00069 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00008 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(ii) Providing technical assistance related to accreditation to institutions, programs, or both; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Policies, evaluative criteria, and procedures, and has made evaluative decisions, that are accepted throughout
the United States by_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Educators and educational institutions; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Licensing bodies, practitioners, and employers in the professional or vocational fields for which the educational
institutions or programs within the agency's jurisdiction prepare their students. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.23 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Application of standards. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) To be listed by the Secretary as a nationally recognized accrediting agency, an accrediting agency must demonstrate
to the Secretary that it consistently applies and enforces written standards that ensure that the education or training
offered by an institution or program is of sufficient quality to achieve, for the duration of any accreditation period
granted by the agency, the stated objective for which it is offered. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The Secretary considers that an accrediting agency meets the requirements of paragraph (a) of this section if_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The agency's written standards and procedures for accreditation and preaccreditation, if that latter status
is offered, comply with the requirements of this part; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The agency's preaccreditation standards, if offered, are appropriately related to the agency's accreditation
standards, with a limit on preaccreditation status of no more than five years for any institution or program; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The agency's organizations, functions, and procedures include effective controls against the inconsistent
application of its criteria and standards; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The agency bases its decisions regarding accreditation or preaccreditation on its published criteria; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) The agency maintains a systematic program of review designed to ensure that its criteria and standards are appropriate
and sufficiently comprehensive to evaluate the quality of the education or training provided by the institutions
or programs it accredits and are relevant to the education or training needs of affected students. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.24 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Accreditation processes.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a)(1) To be listed by the Secretary as a nationally recognized accrediting agency, an accrediting agency must demonstrate
to the Secretary that it has effective mechanisms for evaluating compliance with its standards and those mechanisms
cover the full range of an institution's or program's offerings, including those offerings conducted at branch campuses
and additional locations. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The Secretary considers that an accrediting agency meets the requirements of paragraph (a) of this section if
it meets the requirements contained in paragraphs (b) through (f) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b)(1) In determining whether to grant initial or renewed accreditation, the accrediting agency evaluates whether
an institution or program_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Maintains clearly specified educational objectives consistent with its mission and appropriate in light of
the degrees or certificates it awards; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Is successful in achieving its stated objectives; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Maintains degree and certificate requirements that at least conform to commonly accepted standards; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Complies with the agency's criteria. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) In reaching its determination to grant initial or renewed accreditation, the accrediting agency_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Requires an in-depth self-study by each institution or program in accordance with guidance provided by the agency,
with particular focus on the assessment of educational quality and the continuing improvement of educational quality;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Conducts at least one on-site review of the institution or program at which the agency obtains sufficient information
to enable it to determine if the institution or program complies with the agency's criteria; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Conducts its own analyses and evaluations of the self-study and supporting documentation furnished by the
institution or program, and any other appropriate information from other sources, to determine whether the institution
or program complies with the agency's standards; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Provides to the institution or program a detailed written report on its review assessing_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00070 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00008 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(A) The institution's or program's compliance with the agency's standards, including areas needing improvement;
and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) The institution's or program's performance with respect to student achievement. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) In addition to the on-site visit described in paragraph (b)(2)(ii) of this section, an institutional accrediting
agency whose accreditation enables the institutions it accredits to seek eligibility to participate in Title IV,
HEA programs conducts_during the interval between the agency's award of accreditation or preaccreditation to the
institution or program and the expiration of the accreditation or preaccreditation period_at least one unannounced
on-site review at each institution that provides prebaccalaureate vocational education or training for the purpose
of determining the institution's or program's continued compliance with the agency's standards. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) The accrediting agency_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Monitors institutions or programs throughout the accreditation or preaccreditation period to ensure continuing
compliance with the agency's standards or criteria; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Conducts special evaluations, site visits, or both, as necessary. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) The accrediting agency regularly reevaluates institutions or programs that have been granted accreditation
or preaccreditation. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.25 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Additions to or substantive changes in educational programs. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) To be listed by the Secretary as a nationally recognized accrediting agency, an accrediting agency must demonstrate
to the Secretary that, except as provided in paragraph (b) of this section, it includes within its previous grant of
accreditation or preaccreditation to an institution an educational program that an institution initially offers,
or substantively changes after that grant of accreditation or preaccreditation, only after_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The institution notifies the accrediting agency of the addition of the new program or the substantive change in
the existing program; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The accrediting agency evaluates the new or substantively changed program and determines that it does not adversely
affect the institution's capacity to meet the agency's standards. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) An accrediting agency may extend accreditation to an educational program that an institution initially offers
or substantively changes after it received the agency's last grant of accreditation or preaccreditation without
specifically evaluating and approving that program if_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The institution notifies the agency of that program; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The program does not provide prebaccalaureate vocational education. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00071 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00008 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(c) For purposes of this section, an accrediting agency defines a substantive change in an educational program, but
the definition must include_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) A substantial change in the number of clock or credit hours, the number of weeks, and the content of that program;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) A change in the type of program offered; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) A change in the credential awarded for the successful completion of the program; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) A change from clock hours to credit hours or 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
vice versa.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=3 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=3 -->
&sect;602.26
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=3 -->
Required accreditation standards. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
(a)(1) To be listed by the Secretary as a nationally recognized accrediting agency, an accrediting agency must demonstrate
to the Secretary that its accreditation or preaccreditation standards, or both, are sufficiently rigorous to ensure
that the agency is a reliable authority as to the quality of the education or training provided by the institutions
or programs it accredits. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) For a programmatic accrediting agency that does not serve as an institutional accrediting agency for any of the
programs it accredits, the standards must address the areas contained in paragraph (b) of this section in terms of
the type and level of the program rather than in terms of the institution. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) If none of the institutions an agency accredits participates in any Title IV, HEA program, or if the agency only
accredits programs within institutions accredited by an accrediting agency recognized by the Secretary, the accrediting
agency is not required to have the standards described in paragraphs (b)(7), (b)(8), (b)(10), (b)(12), and (b)(13)
of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) In order to assure that an accrediting agency is a reliable authority as to the quality of the education or training
provided by an institution or program it accredits, the agency must have standards that effectively address the quality
of an institution or program in the following areas: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Curricula. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Faculty. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Facilities, equipment, and supplies. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Fiscal and administrative capacity as appropriate to the specified scale of operations. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The agency shall_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Have standards addressing the institution's or program's finances and management that enable it to assess an
institution's or program's fiscal and administrative capacity, as appropriate to its scale of operations, for the
purpose of determining whether_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) The institution or program appears able to continue to be an ongoing, economically viable entity; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) The finances of the institution or program appear to be sufficient for it to continue to meet the agency's standards;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Make a determination under this standard_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) When it initially evaluates an institution or program for accreditation or preaccreditation; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) When it periodically reevaluates the institution or program for accreditation or preaccreditation; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Require an institution or program to submit on an annual basis sufficient financial information, which may
include the annual audited financial statement the institution or program submits to the Secretary under the Title
IV, HEA programs, to enable the agency to determine if the financial capacity of the institution threatens the ability
of the institution or program to continue to meet the agency's standards; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Review, as appropriate on an annual basis, the information obtained under paragraph (b)(4)(iii) of this section
to determine if there is reason to take any follow-up action based on a reduced financial capacity. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Student support services. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Recruiting and admissions practices, academic calendars, catalogs, publications, grading, and advertising.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The agency shall have standards that enable it to assess an institution's or program's recruiting and admissions
practices, academic calendars, catalogs, publications, grading, and advertising in terms of_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Whether the institution's or program's academic calendar, catalogs, publications, and advertising are accurate,
complete, and consistent with actual practice and agency standards, particularly with respect to costs, financial
obligations, refunds, graduation rates, employment prospects, and other statements regarding educational effectiveness;
and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00072 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00008 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(ii) Whether the institution's or program's admissions policies and standards are reasonable in light of the institution's
or program's educational mission. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Program length and tuition and fees in relation to the subject matters taught and the objectives of the degrees or credentials
offered.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The agency shall have standards that establish minimum and maximum program lengths for prebaccalaureate vocational
education programs and have other standards to enable the agency to assess an institution's or program's length of
program and tuition and fee charges. In developing these standards, the agency shall take into account such factors
as_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Program objectives and content; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The types and locations of instructional delivery; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) The knowledge and skills necessary for students to reach competence in the field being taught; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Generally accepted practices in higher education; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) Any applicable Federal statutes or regulations; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vi) For any prebaccalaureate vocational education program, consideration of the remuneration that can reasonably
be expected by students who complete the program. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(8) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Measures of program length in clock hours or credit hours.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The agency shall have standards that enable it to assess an institution's or program's measurement of program length.
In developing these standards, the agency shall take into account such factors as_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Program goals, objectives, and content; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The types and combinations of instructional methodologies and delivery systems, including outside preparation
as appropriate; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) The knowledge and skills necessary for students to reach competence in the field being taught; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Generally accepted practices in higher education; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) Any applicable Federal statutes or regulations. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(9) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Success with respect to student achievement in relation to mission.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The agency shall have standards that enable it to assess an institution's or program's success with respect 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to student achievement. Under these standards, the agency 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
shall_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Require the institution or program to document and assess the educational achievement of students in verifiable
and consistent ways, such as_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) Student grades, grade point averages, theses, or portfolios; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) Results of admissions tests for graduate or professional school or other standardized tests; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(C) Transfer rates to institutions offering higher level programs; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(D) Job placement rates, completion rates, results of licensing examinations, evaluations by employers, follow-up
studies of alumni, and other recognized measures of educational outcomes; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Require the institution or program to use effectively the information obtained under paragraph (b)(9)(i) of
this section to improve student achievement with respect to the degrees or certificates offered; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Systematically monitor institutional or program performance with respect to student achievement to determine
if performance is consistent with both the institution's or program's mission and objectives and the agency's objective
measures of performance of student achievement; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) For any prebaccalaureate vocational education program accredited by the agency or provided by an institution
the agency accredits, establish minimum quantitative standards for_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) Completion rates; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) Job placement rates; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(C) Pass rates on State licensing examinations or other appropriate measures of occupational competency. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(10) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Default rates in the student loan programs established under Title IV of the Act, based on the most recent data provided
by the Secretary.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The agency shall have standards that require it to evaluate an institution to determine whether the institution is
out of compliance with its accrediting standards if the institution's latest cohort default rate under the Federal
Stafford Loan or Federal Supplemental Loans for Students program_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Equals or exceeds 25 percent; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Has increased significantly in relation to its rate in the previous year. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(11) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Record of student complaints received by, or available to, the agency.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The agency shall have standards that enable it to assess an institution's or program's record of student complaints
received by or made available to the agency. Under these standards, the agency shall_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Review student complaints that relate to the agency's standards; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Take appropriate follow-up action with regard to those complaints; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) If considered necessary by the agency, refer complainants to appropriate Federal, State, and other agencies
if the complaints do not relate to the agency's standards; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Require institutions or programs to make available to students the agency's mailing address or telephone number
for complaints. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(12) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Compliance with the institution's program responsibilities under Title IV of the Act.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The agency shall have standards that require institutions to be in compliance with their responsibilities under
the Title IV, HEA programs. The agency's assessment under these standards shall be based on program reviews, financial
and compliance audits, audited financial statements, and any other information that the Secretary provides. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(13) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
The institution's practice of making refunds to students.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The agency shall have_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) A refund policy, that must be approved by the Secretary, that provides for a fair and equitable refund to a student
of tuition, fees, and other institutional charges; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Standards that enable it to assess whether an institution complies with its refund policy. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00073 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00008 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(c)(1) An accrediting agency shall take appropriate action if its review of an institution or program under any standard
indicates that the institution or program is not in compliance with that standard.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) If the agency believes that the institution or program is not in compliance with the standards, the agency shall_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Take prompt adverse action against the institution or program; or
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Require the institution or program to take appropriate action to bring itself into compliance, or to ensure its
continued compliance, with the agency's standards within a time frame specified by the agency.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The accrediting agency has sole discretion to determine the time frame specified in paragraph (c)(2)(ii) of this
section for the institution or program to bring itself into compliance with agency standards. However, except as
indicated in paragraph (c)(4) of this section, the specified period may not exceed 18 months.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) If the institution or program does not bring itself into compliance within the specified period, the agency must
take adverse action unless the agency extends the period for achieving compliance for good cause.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) An accrediting agency shall have a reasonable basis for determining that the information it relies on for making
the assessments described in paragraphs (b) and (c) of this section is accurate. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) An accrediting agency that has established and applies the standards in paragraph (b) of this section may establish
any additional accreditation standards as it deems appropriate.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1091, 1099b)
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.27 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Additional required operating procedures.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) To be listed by the Secretary as a nationally recognized accrediting agency, an accrediting agency must demonstrate
to the Secretary that it satisfies the procedural requirements contained in other provisions of this part and the
additional requirements contained in paragraphs (b) through (h) of this section.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) If the accrediting agency accredits institutions and that accreditation enables those institutions to seek
eligibility to participate in Title IV, HEA programs_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The agency requires the institution to_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Notify the agency if the institution plans to establish a branch campus or an additional location; and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Submit a business plan described in paragraph (b)(2) of this section if the institution plans to operate a branch
campus or additional location_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) That is geographically apart from the main campus;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) That has its own separate administrative structure, services, and facilities, and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(C) At which the institution plans to offer a complete educational program;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00074 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00008 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(2) The business plan that an institution submits under paragraph (b)(1)(ii) of this section must contain a description
of_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) The educational program to be offered at the branch campus or location;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The projected revenues and expenditures and cash flow at the branch campus or location; and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) The operation, management, and physical resources at the branch campus or location;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The agency extends accreditation to the branch campus or additional location only after evaluating the business
plan and taking other necessary actions to permit the agency to determine that the branch campus or additional location
has sufficient educational, financial, operational, management, and physical resources to satisfy the accrediting
agency's standards for accreditation;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The agency undertakes a site visit of the branch campus or additional location as soon as practicable, but no later
than six months after the establishment of that branch campus or additional location;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) The agency undertakes a site visit of an institution that has undergone a change of ownership that resulted in a
change of control as soon as practicable, but no later than six months after the change of ownership; and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) The agency requires any institution it accredits that enters into a teach-out agreement with another institution
to submit to the accrediting agency for approval a teach-out agreement that is consistent with applicable standards
and regulations.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The accrediting agency maintains and makes publicly available written materials describing_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Each type of accreditation and preaccreditation granted by the agency;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Its procedures for applying for accreditation or preaccreditation;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The criteria and procedures used by the agency for determining whether to grant, reaffirm, reinstate, deny, restrict,
revoke, or take any other action related to each type of accreditation and preaccreditation that the agency grants;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The names, academic and professional qualifications, and relevant employment and organizational affiliations
of the members of the agency's policy and decisionmaking bodies as well as the agency's principal administrative
staff; and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) The institutions or programs that the agency currently accredits or preaccredits and the date when the agency
will review or reconsider the accreditation or preaccreditation of each institution or program.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) In accordance with agency policy, the accrediting agency publishes the year when an institution or program subject
to its jurisdiction is being considered for accreditation or preaccreditation and provides an opportunity for public
comment concerning the institution's or program's qualifications for accreditation or preaccreditation.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
