<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00100 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00009 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=25 g=1 f=1 -->
Enrolled 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Federal Pell Grant Program 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Federal Perkins Loan Program 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Federal PLUS Program 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Federal Stafford Loan Program 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Federal Supplemental Educational Opportunity Grant (FSEOG) Program 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Federal Supplemental Loans for Students (SLS) Program 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Federal Work-Study (FWS) Program 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
National Early Intervention Scholarship and Partnership (NEISP) Program 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
State 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
State Student Incentive Grant (SSIG) Program 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(c) The following definitions apply to terms used in this part: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Classification of Instructional Programs (CIP): 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
A manual published by the U.S. Department of Education, National Center for Education Statistics, that lists the
codes, titles, and descriptions of instructional programs used by institutions and States for reporting and analyzing
education data at the national level. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Education and general expenditures: 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The total amount expended by an institution for instruction, research, public service, academic support (including
library expenditures), student services, institutional support, scholarships and fellowships, operation and
maintenance expenditures for the physical plant, and any mandatory transfers which the institution is required
to pay by law. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
National Occupational Information Coordinating Committee 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(NOICC): An agency jointly sponsored by the Departments of Education and Labor to facilitate comparisons between
educational programs and related occupations and to provide information to State employment counseling services.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Professional program: 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
An undergraduate or graduate educational program that prepares individuals for an occupation, if that occupation_

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Is listed in SOC or CIP; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Requires at least an associate degree to qualify for entry; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Involves the independent practice or application of a defined or organized body of competencies that is unique
to the occupation; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Is formally recognized and regulated under a national or State licensure, accreditation, or permit system.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Referred institution: 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
An institution that a SPRE reviews as a result of_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) A referral by the Secretary under &sect;667.5; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) State selection under &sect;667.6. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Standard Occupational Classification (SOC) Manual: 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
A manual published by the U.S. Department of Commerce, used for reporting national statistics on occupations and
employment projections, compiled from data collected through the census and other Federal surveys. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
State Postsecondary Review Entity (SPRE): 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The entity described in &sect;667.4. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Title IV, HEA program: 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
One of the programs identified in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
34 CFR 668.1. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Vocational program: 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
An educational program below the baccalaureate degree level, that is not classified as a professional program, that
prepares students for gainful employment in a recognized occupation. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099a&hyph;1099a&hyph;3) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;667.3 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
State agreement. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) To participate in the State Postsecondary Review Program, a State must enter into an agreement with the Secretary.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) In the agreement, the State_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Designates a SPRE; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Describes the organizational structure of the SPRE; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Assures that_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) The SPRE has the legal authority under State law to carry out the functions required of it under this part; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The SPRE will perform the functions required of it under this part; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) The SPRE will keep records or have access to records and provide information to the Secretary as may be requested
for financial and compliance audits, and program evaluations; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) The SPRE will review referred institutions on a schedule that coincides with the Secretary's schedule for recertifying
those institutions to participate in the Title IV, HEA programs; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00101 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00009 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(4) Describes the relationship between the SPRE, the State approving agency for Veterans Affairs, the State guaranty
agency under the FFEL programs, the State agency responsible for administering the SSIG Program, any State entity
that provides a license to institutions to operate in the State or otherwise legally authorizes institutions to provide
postsecondary education in the State, any State-level entity that approves service providers under the Job Training
Partnership Act, and any State-level entity that certifies vocational education; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Indicates that the SPRE_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Shall contract with a nationally recognized accrediting agency or a peer review system for purposes of &sect;667.23;
and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) May contract with a private agency, nationally recognized accrediting agency, or peer review system for assistance
in performing the SPRE's functions; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Includes the SPRE's plan for performing the functions described in &sect;667.12. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The agreement between the State and the Secretary goes into effect when it is signed by the Secretary and remains
in effect until it is terminated by the Secretary or the State. The Secretary or the State terminates an agreement under
the provisions of that agreement. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) The sanctions set forth in paragraph (e) of this section follow if the State_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Does not enter into an agreement with the Secretary; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Fails to comply with the terms of the agreement and the Secretary terminates that agreement; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Terminates the agreement with the Secretary; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Does not establish review standards under &sect;667.21 that are approved by the Secretary by the end of the second
year for which the State received an allotment under &sect;667.11. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) If any of the events listed in paragraph (d) of this section occur_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The State is ineligible to receive_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Any funds appropriated to carry out this program; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Its allotment of any funds appropriated under the SSIG Program; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Any funds appropriated to carry out the NEISP Program; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The Secretary_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Does not designate as eligible for participation in a Title IV, HEA program any institution seeking initial participation
in that program, any branch campus for which an institution seeks an initial designation of eligibility under 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
34 CFR part 600, or any institution that has undergone a change in ownership that results in a change in control as determined
in 34 CFR part 600, that is located in that State; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Grants only provisional certification, as determined in 34 CFR part 668, to an institution in that State not described
in paragraph (e)(2)(i) of this section; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) May_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) Establish the review standards for that State described in &sect;667.21; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) Carry out, or arrange to carry out, the State's other responsibilities and requirements under this part.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099a&hyph;1) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;667.4
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
State postsecondary review entity. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The SPRE is the entity designated by the State in the agreement between the State and the Secretary under &sect;667.3,
to_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) Represent all existing State entities that are, and all future State entities that will be, responsible for_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Granting State authorization to provide postsecondary education in that State; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Ensuring that all institutions in the State that participate in a Title IV, HEA program remain in compliance with
the State review standards established under &sect;667.21; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Perform the functions required of it under this part; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) Keep records or have access to records and provide information to the Secretary as may be requested for financial
and compliance audits, and program evaluations.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099a&hyph;1099a&hyph;3) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;667.5
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Criteria the Secretary uses to refer institutions to a SPRE for review. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a)(1) The Secretary refers an institution that participates in a Title IV, HEA program to a SPRE for review if the institution
meets one or more of the criteria contained in paragraph (b) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00102 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00009 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(2) In determining whether an institution meets one or more of the criteria contained in paragraph (b) of this section,
the Secretary uses the most recently available data. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Except as provided in paragraphs (c), (d), and (e) of this section, the Secretary refers an institution to a SPRE
if_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The institution has a cohort default rate (defined in 34 CFR 668.15) equal to or greater than 25 percent; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2)(i) The institution has a cohort default rate equal to or greater than 20 percent; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) During the latest completed award year for which data are available_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) More than two-thirds of the institution's regular undergraduate students who were enrolled as at least half-time
students received assistance under any Title IV, HEA program, excluding assistance received from the SSIG, NEISP,
and Federal PLUS Programs; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) The amount that the institution's students received under the Title IV, HEA programs, excluding funds from the
SSIG, NEISP, and Federal PLUS Programs, is equal to or greater than two-thirds of the institution's education and
general expenditures; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The amount that the institution's students received under the Federal Pell Grant Program is equal to or greater
than two-thirds of the institution's education and general expenditures; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The Secretary initiated a limitation, suspension, or termination action against the institution under 34 CFR
part 668, subpart G, within the preceding 5 years; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) An audit finding in the institution's two most recent audits under 34 CFR 668.23 resulted in a required repayment
by the institution of an amount greater than 5 percent of the funds the institution received under the Title IV, HEA
programs for any one award year covered by those audits; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) The Secretary cited the institution for its failure to submit an audit report by the deadlines established under

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
34 CFR 668.23; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7)(i) The amount that the institution's students received under the Federal Pell Grant Program during any award
year differed by more than 25 percent from the amount those students received under that program in the award year that
preceded that award year, unless the differences can be accounted for by changes in that program; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The amount that the institution's students received under the Federal Stafford Loan Program during any award
year differs by more than 25 percent from the amount those students received under that program in the award year that
preceded that award year, unless the differences can be accounted for by changes in that program; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) The amount that the institution's students received under the Federal SLS Program during any award year differs
by more than 25 percent from the amount those students received under that program in the award year that preceded that
award year, unless the differences can be accounted for by changes in that program; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(8) The institution failed to meet the financial responsibility standards in 34 CFR part 668, subpart B; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(9) The institution underwent a change in ownership that resulted in a change of control as defined in 34 CFR 600.31;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(10) Except with regard to any public institution affiliated with a State system of higher education, the institution
has participated for less than 5 years in_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) The Federal Pell Grant Program; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The FFEL programs; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) The FSEOG Program; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) The FWS Program; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) The Federal Perkins Loan Program; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(11) The institution has been subject to a pattern of complaints from students, faculty, or others, including information
provided to the Secretary by the SPRE, related to its management or conduct of the Title IV, HEA programs or to misleading
or inappropriate advertising and promotion of the institution's educational programs, that in the Secretary's
judgment are sufficient to warrant review. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) If the Secretary refers an institution to the SPRE under paragraph (b)(9) with regard to the same change of ownership
or (b)(6) of this section, and the SPRE conducts a review of the institution as a result of that referral and finds no
significant violations of the State's standards, the Secretary reserves whether to refer that institution again
to the SPRE for the same reason that resulted in the initial referral. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) The Secretary reserves whether to refer again to the SPRE an institution that meets only the conditions of paragraph
(b)(10) of this section, if the SPRE previously conducted a review of that institution and found no violations of the
State's standards. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e)(1) An institution may request the Secretary to confirm the data used by the Secretary in referring that institution
to a SPRE. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The Secretary rescinds a referral if confirmation reveals that the data used to make a referral was inaccurate
and a referral would not be required under accurate data. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The Secretary does not rescind a referral if the Secretary_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Confirms that the data are accurate; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Is unable to confirm the data. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) In confirming data, the Secretary presumes that records maintained in the normal course of business by the U.S.
Department of Education, a guaranty agency under the FFEL programs, a SPRE, a State licensing agency, or another State
agency are accurate unless the institution proves to the Secretary's satisfaction that the records are not properly
maintained or are inaccurate.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099a&hyph;3) 
