<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;667.6 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
SPRE selection of institutions for review. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
A SPRE may review an institution under this part that was not referred by the Secretary if_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) The SPRE_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1)(i) Determines that the institution meets a referral criterion in &sect;667.5 based on more recent data available
to the SPRE; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Has reason to believe the institution is engaged in fraudulent practices; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Requests the Secretary to approve its review of that institution; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The Secretary_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Approves that request; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Does not respond to the SPRE's request within 21 days after the date the Secretary receives that request. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099a&hyph;3) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;667.7 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Notice to SPRE of Federal actions. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) If the Secretary takes an action against an institution, the Secretary notifies the SPRE of the State in which the
institution is located within 10 days of taking that action. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) If the Secretary is informed that another Federal agency is taking an action against an institution, the Secretary
notifies the SPRE of the State in which the institution is located as soon as possible but not later than 10 days after
learning of that action. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099a&hyph;3) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;667.8 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Institutions with locations in more than one State. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) If an institution that is subject to a referral has locations in more than one State, the Secretary refers the institution
to the SPRE in each State in which the institution is located and informs each SPRE of the other States in which the institution
is located. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The SPRE of the State in which the main campus of the institution is located has the principal responsibility for
reviewing that institution. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) If a branch campus or additional location of an institution is in a State other than the State in which the institution's
main campus is located, the SPRE of the State in which that branch campus or additional location is located_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) May review that branch campus or additional location before a SPRE review is conducted of the main campus of that
institution; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) May delay its review of that branch campus or additional location until a SPRE review is conducted of the main campus
of that institution; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) May choose not to review that branch campus or additional location if_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) The SPRE of the State in which the main campus of that institution is located reviews that institution and makes
no significant findings; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The State's allotment is insufficient to allow the SPRE to review all referred institutions. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) An institution, its branch campuses, and additional locations are subject to the review standards of the State
in which they are located. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) Notwithstanding paragraphs (b) and (c) of this section, to review a referred institution that has locations in
more than one State, the SPREs of those States may enter into an agreement under which the SPREs may alter the review
responsibilities set forth in paragraphs (b) and (c) of this section. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099a&hyph;3) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=52 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpart B_Allotment Formula and Funding Procedures 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;667.11 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Allotment formula. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) For each fiscal year for which funds are appropriated to carry out this part: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The Secretary_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Allots $20,000 to Guam, $20,000 to American Samoa, $20,000 to the Northern Mariana Islands, $20,000 to the Virgin
Islands, and $20,000 to the Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Calculates each remaining State's allotment of the remaining funds under paragraph (a)(2) of this section;
and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Notifies each State of its allotment. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Except for Guam, American Samoa, the Northern Mariana Islands, the Virgin Islands, and the Trust Territory of
the Pacific Islands, the Secretary allots those funds to a State by_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Determining the percentage of institutions participating in a Title IV, HEA program in the State by dividing the
number of institutions located in that State that are certified to participate in a Title IV, HEA program by the total
number of institutions that are certified to participate in all States; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) For the latest award year for which information is available, determining the percentage of Title IV, HEA program
funds by dividing the total amount of Title IV, HEA program funds that were made available to students who enrolled
in the institutions in that State that participate in a Title IV, HEA program, or to those students' parents, by the
total amount of Title IV, HEA program funds that were made available to students, or to those student's parents, who
enrolled in institutions that participate in a Title IV, HEA program in all States; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Averaging the two percentages determined in paragraph (a)(2)(i) and (ii) of this section; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Calculating an ``initial distribution'' by multiplying the average percentage determined in paragraph (a)(2)(iii)
of this section by the amount appropriated to carry out this part less the total amount allotted to Guam, American Samoa,
the Northern Mariana Islands, the Virgin Islands, and the Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v)(A) Determining which States receive less than $50,000 under the initial distribution; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) Providing each of those States with $50,000; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(C) Calculating the difference between the $50,000 provided to each of those States and those States' initial distribution;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vi)(A) Determining which States receive more than $50,000 under the initial distribution; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00104 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00009 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(B) Calculating the difference between each of those States' initial distribution and $50,000; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vii) Calculating a ``reduction percentage'' by dividing the total amount obtained in paragraph (a)(2)(v)(C) of
this section by the total amount obtained in paragraph (a)(2)(vi)(B) of this section; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(viii) Reducing the initial distribution of each State in paragraph (a)(2)(vi)(A) of this section by the product
of the amount obtained in paragraph (a)(2)(vi)(B) of this section and the reduction percentage in paragraph (a)(2)(vii)
of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) If the Secretary determines that a SPRE will not spend its entire allotment during the period for which those funds
are made available, or if a SPRE does not spend its allotment by the end of the period for which those funds are made available,
the Secretary reallots those funds to other SPREs in a manner that the Secretary determines best carries out the purposes
of the State Postsecondary Review Program. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) SSIG and NEISP Program Federal and State matching funds are excluded from the calculations in this section. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099a&hyph;1099a&hyph;3) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;667.12 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Application for funds. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a)(1) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
General.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 For each fiscal year for which funds are appropriated to carry out this part, a State that has entered into an agreement
with the Secretary under &sect;667.3 shall apply to the Secretary to receive its allotment. The State's application
must contain the information required in paragraph (b), (c), or (d) of this section, as appropriate. The Secretary
publishes in the 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=4 -->
Federal Register
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 the date by which a State must submit its application. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Established review standards.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 A State has established review standards if those standards met the requirements in &sect;667.21 and the Secretary
did not disapprove those standards under &sect;667.22. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Application before standards are established. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) If a State has not established review standards, to receive its allotment the State_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Must submit a plan to develop_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) The review standards described in &sect;667.21, in consultation with the institutions in that State, which shall
describe the manner in which consultation will take place; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) The procedures for receiving and responding to complaints from students, faculty, and others regarding institutions
in the State, in consultation with institutions in that State, which shall describe the manner in which consultation
will take place; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) May submit a plan to identify information maintained by institutions and State agencies, other than the information
institutions are required to maintain under the Student Right-to-Know and Campus Security Act, that is relevant
to developing the State review standards, to identify systems in which this information is maintained, and to provide
estimates of the costs of coordinating the institutions' and State's information systems with an information system
developed by the SPRE; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00105 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00009 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
(iii) Must submit a budget for developing the standards and the complaint procedures and for providing cost estimates
for the SPRE's information system, if relevant, that does not exceed the State's fiscal year 1993 allotment. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) If the State's fiscal year 1993 allotment is less than the State's anticipated cost of carrying out the activities
described in paragraphs (b)(1) (i) and (ii) of this section, the State shall first use its allotment to develop the
review standards. If a portion of the allotment remains after the State develops its review standards, the State may
develop procedures for receiving and responding to complaints from students, faculty, and others regarding institutions
in the State. The State may use any remaining portion of its allotment to provide cost estimates for the SPRE's information
system only after it has completed developing its review standards and complaint procedures. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) Application after standards are established.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) If the Secretary has not disapproved the State's review standards under &sect;667.22, to receive its allotment,
the State must submit to the Secretary_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Its plan to review referred institutions; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) A budget for those reviews that does not exceed the State's allotment calculated under &sect;667.11 less any
amount expended by the SPRE in carrying out the activities under paragraph (b) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) If a SPRE anticipates that the cost of reviewing all the referred institutions will exceed the State's allotment,
the SPRE shall, as part of its plan, submit a priority system for selecting institutions to review from among the referred
institutions. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (3) The SPRE shall have discretion in developing its priority system, except that the SPRE must make its top priority
for review, referred institutions that the Secretary has scheduled for recertification under 34 CFR part 668, subpart
B. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) If a State first applies to the Secretary to receive an allotment after fiscal year 1993, the State must submit the
information and documentation required under paragraph (b) of this section, and may submit the information required
in paragraph (c) of this section.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099a&hyph;1099a&hyph;3) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;667.13 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Approval of funding application. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Before standards are established.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The Secretary approves a State's plan and budget submitted before the State establishes review standards if_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The plan provides a reasonable basis, and adequate budget justification, for carrying out the activities described
in &sect;667.12(b)(1); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) If applicable, the plan includes a priority system for using the State's allotment as described in &sect;667.12(b)(2);
and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The budget includes only reasonable allowable costs within the State's fiscal year 1993 allotment. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
After standards are established.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 After the State establishes review standards, the Secretary approves a State's plan and budget for the allowable
activities described in &sect;667.14 if_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The plan provides adequate budget justification for those activities; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The plan provides for a reasonable scheme for reviewing referred institutions; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The plan includes a priority system for review as described in &sect;667.12(c)(3); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The proposed contracts with private agencies, accrediting agencies, or peer review systems to carry out SPRE
functions included in the plan are reasonable and appropriate; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) The budget includes only reasonable allowable costs within the State's allotment. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Failure to submit an acceptable application.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 If a State does not submit an application for funds under &sect;667.12 or its application is not approved under this
section_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (1) The State is ineligible to receive_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Any funds appropriated to carry out this program; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Its allotment of any funds appropriated under the SSIG Program; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Any funds appropriated to carry out the NEISP Program; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The Secretary_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Does not designate as eligible for participation in a Title IV, HEA program any institution seeking initial participation
in that program, any branch campus for which an institution seeks an initial designation of eligibility under 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
34 CFR part 600, or any institution that has undergone a change in ownership that results in a change in control as determined
in 34 CFR part 600, that is located in that State; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Grants only provisional certification, as determined in 34 CFR part 668, to an institution in that State not described
in paragraph (c)(2)(i) of this section.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099a&hyph;1099a&hyph;3) 
