<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(b) If a State seeks reimbursement for indirect costs, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the State shall_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Use the restricted indirect cost rate, computed under 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
34 CFR 75.564, and approved by the Secretary under 34 CFR 75.561; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Not charge as a direct cost any cost that qualifies as an indirect cost. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The direct costs of carrying out the activities described in paragraph (a) of this section include, but are not
limited to_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The salary of State employees engaged in allowable activities; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Travel costs incurred_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Consulting with institutions in developing standards and complaint procedures; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Reviewing referred institutions; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Training for_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) State employees to perform reviews of referred institutions; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Institutional and other personnel regarding the State review standards; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Contracting with private organizations, accrediting agencies, and peer review systems to carry out required
activities; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Costs incurred by the State for administrative actions and legal proceedings.
