<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;667.15 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Fiscal procedures and records. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (a) A State must account for the funds it received under this part in accordance with the procedures it uses to account
for the expenditure of its own funds and must keep fiscal and accounting records that support, on audit, its expenditure
of funds under this part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (b) (1) Except as provided in paragraph (b)(2) of this section, the State must keep intact and accessible records relating
to its activities under this part for five years after the end of the period for which funds were provided. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (2) The State shall keep records on any claim or expenditure questioned on audit until any audit question is resolved.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) A State must have an audit performed of the SPRE's activities under this part at least once every two years and must
submit that audit to the Secretary. An audit conducted under the Single Audit Act satisfies this requirement.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099a&hyph;1099a&hyph;3) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;667.16 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Supplement, not supplant, requirement. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The Secretary reimburses a State for the costs of necessary SPRE activities which supplement, but do not supplant,
existing licensing or review functions conducted by the State.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099a&hyph;2) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=56 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpart C_State Review Standards, SPRE Reviews, and Termination of Institutional Participation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
 &sect;667.21 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
State review standards. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Each State participating under this part must develop standards, in consultation with institutions in the State,
under which the SPRE reviews referred institutions. The State-developed review standards must evaluate, with regard
to a referred institution_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The extent to which the institution makes available to its students and prospective students its catalogs, admission
requirements, course outlines, tuition and fee schedules, refund policy, course cancellation policy, its rules
and regulations, and its enrollment agreement if appropriate; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Whether the institution's descriptions of its courses and programs are accurate; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Whether the institution has a method to assess that a student has the ability to complete successfully the educational
program for which he or she applies; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The extent to which the institution's method to assess that a student has the ability to complete successfully
the educational program for which he or she applies accurately assesses that ability as measured by the completion
rate of that program; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Whether the institution maintains and enforces standards relating to satisfactory progress; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Whether the institution maintains adequate student and other records; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00107 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00009 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(7) Whether the institution complies with relevant safety, and health standards, such as fire, building, and sanitation
codes; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(8) The extent to which the institution's financial and administrative capacity is appropriate to its scale of operations,
and whether the institution maintains adequate financial and other information to determine the adequacy of its
financial and administrative capacity; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(9) For an institution that the SPRE determines is at financial risk, the adequacy of the institution's plans to provide
for, if the institution closes_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Instruction to enrolled students; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Retention of and access to academic and financial aid records; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(10) If an institution provides an educational program that is designed to prepare students for gainful employment_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Whether the tuition and fees charged for that educational program are reasonable given the amount of money that
a student who successfully completes the program may reasonably be expected to earn; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Whether the educational program provides students with quality training that leads to useful employment in
an occupation recognized in that State. In making this evaluation, one of the factors the SPRE shall consider is the
appropriateness of the length of the educational program in terms of both the number of days of instruction and the
number of credit or clock hours the program offers; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(11) The extent to which the institution provides to its students relevant information regarding_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Market and job availability for students in its occupational, professional, and vocational programs; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The relationship between the institution's educational programs and State licensing standards for specific
occupations; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(12) The appropriateness of the number of semester, trimester, or quarter credit or clock hours required for the completion
of an educational program; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(13) The appropriateness of the length of 600-hour educational programs; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(14) Whether, and the extent to which, the actions of any owner or shareholder of the institution, or any person exercising
control over the institution may adversely affect its participation in a Title IV, HEA program; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(15) The extent to which the institution's procedures for investigating and resolving student complaints are adequate;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(16) The extent to which the institution's advertising promotion, and student recruiting practices are appropriate;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(17) Whether the institution has a fair and equitable refund policy; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(18) The extent to which the institution's educational programs are successful as measured by_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) The completion and graduation rates of the students enrolled in those programs, taking into account the length
of the program and the selectivity of the institution's admissions policy (for the purpose of this provision, a completion
rate is the same as a graduation rate); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The institution's withdrawal rate; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) With respect to the institution's vocational and professional programs, the placement rate of the institution's
graduates in occupations related to their educational programs, with related programs and occupations determined
by reference to the 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
NOICC CIP/DOT Master Crosswalk;
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Where appropriate, the rate at which the institution's graduates pass licensure examinations; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) The success of the institution's students who express other completion goals, such as transferring to another
institution, full-time employment in their field of study, or military service, in meeting those goals. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) In developing the review standards in paragraph (a) of this section, a State_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) May establish different standards for different types or categories of institutions or educational programs;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Shall specify the records and information an institution would need to maintain to demonstrate to a SPRE the institution's
compliance with those standards; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Except for standards regarding prospective students in paragraph (a)(1) of this section, shall establish standards
that apply at least to all regular students; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Shall quantify the standards described in paragraphs (a)(10)(i) and (a)(18) (i), (ii), (iii), and (iv) of this
section by establishing_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
