<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;667.22 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Disapproval of State review standards. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) (1) Each State shall submit to the Secretary for his evaluation the review standards it developed under &sect;667.21.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The State shall also submit to the Secretary an explanation of how each standard was established, including_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) An explanation of the relationship between each of the State's review standards and the related or comparable
Title IV, HEA standards and requirements; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) If applicable, an explanation of the reasons for establishing different review standards for different types
of institutions or educational programs; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) A description of the manner in which institutions were consulted in developing the review standards. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The Secretary disapproves a State's review standards if_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The State does not assure the Secretary that the State's review standards are consistent with the laws and constitution
of that State; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The State does not submit evidence that the State's review standards were developed in consultation with the institutions
in that State; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The State's review standards do not meet or exceed all of the requirements and cover all the areas described in &sect;667.21;
or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The standards developed under &sect;667.21(b)(4)_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Do not specify the methods and procedures that an institution must use to calculate_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) The relationship between the tuition and fees charged by an institution for an educational program and the amount
of money that a student who successfully completes that program actually earns; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) The graduation or completion rates, withdrawal rates, placement rates, and licensure examination pass rates
of the institution's students or graduates; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00109 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00009 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(ii) Do not specify statistically valid methods and procedures that an institution must use if that institution conducts
surveys of its graduates to obtain data regarding the type of employment, placement, earnings, or licensure examination
pass rates of the institution's graduates; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) If the Secretary disapproves a State's review standards, the Secretary gives the State the reasons for that disapproval
and gives the State an opportunity to_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Demonstrate why the Secretary's disapproval was incorrect; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Submit revised review standards that address the reasons for the Secretary's disapproval. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099a&hyph;3) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;667.23
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
SPRE reviews of institutions. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) If the Secretary refers an institution to a SPRE for review under &sect;667.5 or the SPRE selects an institution
for review under &sect;667.6 and the Secretary approves that selection, the SPRE reviews, or arranges for the review
of that institution, to determine whether the institution is in compliance with the State review standards described
in &sect;667.21. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The SPRE shall provide written notice to all institutions in the State of the review standards approved by the Secretary
under &sect;667.22 before it may conduct reviews of referred institutions. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The SPRE must issue an initial report of its findings and provide it to the institution no later than 45 days after
the SPRE completes its review. If the SPRE finds that the institution is in violation of a standard, for each finding,
the SPRE_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Must cite the standard violated and the nature of the violation; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) May_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Prescribe, if necessary, a course of action the institution must follow to correct the violation. The SPRE has
sole discretion to determine an appropriate period for the institution to correct the violation and bring itself
into compliance with the State's review standards; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Initiate a proceeding under &sect;667.25 to effect the termination of the institution's participation in the

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Title IV, HEA programs. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) The SPRE must give the institution an opportunity to respond to its findings and required actions. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) If the institution chooses to respond within the time permitted by the SPRE, the SPRE must evaluate the institution's
response and issue a final report to the institution that includes its findings and required action. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) (1) The SPRE must provide to the Secretary a copy of its final report to an institution within 30 days of its issuance
to the institution; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) If the institution did not respond to the SPRE's initial report by the date permitted by the SPRE, the SPRE must provide
to the Secretary a copy of its initial report. The SPRE's initial report becomes its final report on the day after the
date provided to the institution for responding to that report; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) If the SPRE did not prescribe a course of action the institution must follow to correct a violation of the State's
standards under paragraph (c) of this section, the SPRE must include in its report to the Secretary an explanation
of why no action was prescribed. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(g) In addition to the reasons for initiating a proceeding to effect the termination an institution's participation
in the Title IV, HEA programs under paragraph (c) of this section, the SPRE may determine that the institution should
no longer participate in the Title IV, HEA programs if that institution_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Does not respond to the SPRE's findings or required actions within the time permitted by the SPRE and the SPRE's
findings show serious violations of the State's standards; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Does not allow SPRE personnel at the institution; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Fails to provide SPRE officials with prompt access to its documents and records. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099a&hyph;3) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;667.24 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Peer reviews of institutions. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) To carry out a review of a referred institution, the SPRE must contract with a nationally recognized accrediting
agency or other peer review system the SPRE determines demonstrates competence in assessing educational programs.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00110 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00009 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(b) (1) Under the contract described in paragraph (a) of this section, the accrediting agency or peer review system
shall carry out a review or provide information from its previous grant of accreditation or previous review to the
SPRE regarding the agency's or system's assessment of the quality and content of the institution's educational programs
in relation to achieving the stated objectives for which the programs were offered. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) In making its assessment under paragraph (b)(1) of this section, for each educational program, the agency or system
shall take into account the adequacy of the space, equipment, instructional materials, staff, and student support
services, including student orientation and counseling provided for each program, and any other areas specified
in the agency's contract with the SPRE. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099a&hyph;3) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;667.25 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Termination of an institution's participation in the Title IV, HEA programs. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) (1) If a SPRE determines that an institution should no longer participate in a Title IV, HEA program, based upon
its review, because the institution is in violation of State standards or has not complied with the SPRE requirements
such as those listed in &sect;667.23(g), the SPRE must provide the institution with the opportunity to contest that
determination in accordance with procedures the Secretary has approved for that purpose under &sect;667.26. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) If the SPRE still concludes after affording the institution the opportunity to challenge the SPRE's initial determination
that the institution is in violation of the State's review standards and should no longer continue to participate
in a Title IV, HEA program, the SPRE notifies the Secretary of those findings and that determination. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) (1) Upon notice by the SPRE that the institution should no longer participate in a Title IV, HEA program, the Secretary
immediately terminates that institution's participation in that program and notifies the institution and the SPRE
of the effective date of that termination. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) If an institution's participation in a Title IV, HEA program is terminated under this section_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) The institution may not appeal that termination to the Secretary; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The institution may not reapply to the Secretary to participate in that program until 18 months have expired from
the effective date of its termination. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099a&hyph;3) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;667.26 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Due process requirements. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Each State shall submit to the Secretary for approval the procedures it uses to allow an institution to challenge
a SPRE's finding that the institution is in violation of the State's review standards and should no longer continue
to participate in a Title IV, HEA program. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The Secretary approves a State's procedures described in paragraph (a) of this section if_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The State review standards are in writing; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The procedures require the SPRE to_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Notify an institution of any required action and the basis for that action; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Permit the institution the opportunity to challenge that adverse action in a hearing or in writing; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Notify the institution in writing of the result of its challenge, and the basis for that result; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Follow other applicable procedural requirements of State law. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099a&hyph;3) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 02 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

