<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 03 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->

<!-- PJG STAG 4704 -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=55 g=1 f=1 -->
Lodging of Consent Decree Pursuant to the Comprehensive Environmental Response, Compensation, and Liability Act
of 1980
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 03 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->

<!-- PJG STAG 4703 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
In accordance with Departmental policy, 28 CFR 50.7, notice is hereby given that on December 21, 1993, proposed Consent
Decrees in 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
United States
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 v. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Jadco, Inc. et al.,
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Civil Action No. 3:92CV&hyph;293&hyph;MU, and 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
United States
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 v. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Hoescht Celanese Corporation et al.,
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Civil Action No. 3:93CV&hyph;412&hyph;MC, were lodged with the United States District Court for the Western District
of North Carolina. The Complaints, brought pursuant to Section 107 of the Comprehensive Environmental Response,
Compensation, and Liability Act of 1980, as amended by the Superfund Amendments and Reauthorization Act of 1986 (``CERCLA''),
42 U.S.C. 9607, seek the recovery of past response costs incurred by the United States in connection with the Jadco-Hughes
Superfund Site, North Belmont, North Carolina (the ``Site''). The Site is situated in Gaston County, North Carolina,
approximately 12 miles west of Charlotte, North Carolina and occupies approximately 6 acres. The Site was used from
1971 until at least 1975 for recovery, storage and disposal of waste solvents and other hazardous substances. These
hazardous wastes were stored on the Site in 55 gallon drums. In some areas of the Site, drums were stacked as many as three
to a stack in deteriorating condition.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The Consent Decree in 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
United States
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 v. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Jadco, Inc. et al.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 provides that the Settling Defendants in that action will pay $227,453.24 in settlement of the United States' claims.
