Lodging of a Consent Decree Pursuant to the Toxic Substances Control Act
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 03 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->

<!-- PJG STAG 4703 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
In accordance with Departmental policy, 28 CFR 50.7, notice is hereby given that on January 7, 1994, a proposed consent
decree in 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
United States 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
v. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
New York State Department of Transportation, 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
No. 89&hyph;CV&hyph;319, was lodged with the United States District Court for the Northern District of New York.
The decree resolves claims of the United States for injunctive relief against the Defendant in the above-referenced
action under the Toxic Substances Control Act (``TSCA'') relating to PCB-contaminated dredged materials at two
areas known as the Buoy 212 Site and the Special Area 13 Site (the ``Sites''). The Buoy 212 Site is located in the Town
of Fort Edward, New York. The Special Area 13 Site is located in the Town of Moreau, New York. In the proposed consent
decree the Defendant agrees to perform site characterization, temporary remedial work, monitoring, maintenance,
and continuing assessment of the future permanent remediation of the Sites. New York State Department of Transportation
has already initiated and/or completed actions required by the Decree.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The proposed decree may be examined at the Environmental Enforcement Section Consent Decree Library, 1120 G Street,
NW., Washington, DC 20005, (202) 624&hyph;0892. A copy of the proposed decree may be obtained in person or by mail from
the Consent Decree Library.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The Department of Justice will receive written comments relating to the proposed consent decree on or before February
23, 1994. Comments should be addressed to Assistant Attorney General, Environment and Natural Resources Division,
Department of Justice, Washington, DC 20530, and should refer to 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
United States 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
v. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
New York State Department of Transportation, 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(DOJ Reference No. 90&hyph;5&hyph;1&hyph;1&hyph;3297).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

