<USDEPT>DEPARTMENT OF STATE</USDEPT>

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=41 g=1 f=1 -->

<RINDOCK>[Public Notice 1935]</RINDOCK>
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->

<!-- PJG STAG 4704 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=55 g=1 f=1 -->
Delegation of Authority No. 209; Under Secretary for Political Affairs 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->

<!-- PJG STAG 4703 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=44 g=1 f=1 -->
January 7, 1994.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
1. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Delegation.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 By virtue of the authority vested in the Secretary of State, including the authority of section 4, of the Act of May 26,
1949 (22 U.S.C. 2658), as amended, I hereby delegate to the Under Secretary for Political Affairs the following: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) Those functions conferred upon the Secretary of State by 18 U.S.C. 3186 relating to ordering delivery of persons
committed under 18 U.S.C. 3184 and 3185 to authorized agents of foreign countries; and, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Those functions conferred upon the Secretary of State by 18 U.S.C. 981(i)(1), 19 U.S.C. 1616a(c)(2), and 21 U.S.C.
881(e)(1)(E), and similar statutes that may be enacted, to approve the transfer of forfeited assets to foreign governments.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
2. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Technical provisions. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Notwithstanding this delegation of authority, the Secretary of State may at any time exercise any function delegated
by this delegation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Any act affected by this delegation shall be deemed to be such act as amended from time to time. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) Nothing herein shall derogate from Department of State Delegation of Authority No. 134, dated March 4, 1976, or
Delegation of Authority No. 202, dated March 23, 1993, which delegated the above-enumerated functions to the Deputy
Secretary of State. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) This delegation of authority to the Under Secretary for Political Affairs shall remain in effect only until such
time as a confirmed nominee assumes the position of Deputy Secretary of State or the President appoints an Acting Deputy
Secretary of State under 5 U.S.C. 3347, at which time this delegation of authority shall expire.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=21 g=1 f=1 -->
Dated: January 7, 1994.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<SIGNER>
<!-- PJG ITAG l=06 g=1 f=1 -->
Warren Christopher, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

